climbs.name: Zenergy
climbs.fa: p1= Lance Milo Cagle, P2 = Cagle, Herm Harrison, Austin Archer

content.description: This route is to the right of the chimney/gully.(P1,10b) - Climb a line of bolts that trends up and left towards a huge golden roof.Crux is just below the big roof. Climb out left side of roof to the 1st belay. From here, (P2, 10c ) - straight up around a left facing corner with a finger crack in the back, leads you to the steep corner/headwall. When the corner ends, clip bolt out left and make an airy traverse move to the anchor.
content.protection: Pitch 1 =13 bolts. Pitch 2 = 10 bolts. Both anchors have "lower offs", and you need a 70m rope to do them.
content.location: From "3 hour arete", skirt the toe of the buttress around to the right.

content.description: On the left hand side of a huge chimney/gully, follow left facing corners up to an airy traverse. A classic bulge 5.9, leads to an airy, easy top out. 70m to lower off.
content.location: From "3 hour arete", skirt the toe of the buttress .
